<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>David Huish, deputy chairman of the Professional Golfers' Association, was  <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">quoted</EVENT> as <EVENT eid="e2" class="REPORTING" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">saying</EVENT>: "If Seve <EVENT eid="e3" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> that to my face I'd <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="FUTURE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">punch</EVENT> him on the nose.&#13;
"I can't <EVENT eid="e5" class="I_STATE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="NEG" modality="none">believe</EVENT> it. If he's <EVENT eid="e6" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PROGRESSIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">suggesting</EVENT> that members of the committee have  been <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">offered</EVENT> inducements I'd <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">take</EVENT> it all the way to the courts. It would be  like <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESPART" aspect="PROGRESSIVE" polarity="POS" modality="would">winning</EVENT> the pools."&#13;
